---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/') ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---
<Layout title="The Pipeline">
  <h1>The pipeline</h1>
  <p>
    Every change to this site — including the one that shipped it live — moves through the same
    AI-assisted path from idea to production:
  </p>
  <pre>Issue → Copilot drafts a PR → Copilot Code Review → Agent Merge →
GitHub Actions (build + supply-chain security + deploy) → GitHub Pages (live site)</pre>
  <p>The loop repeats automatically on every future change. Five capabilities carry it:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><a href={`${base}capabilities/copilot-code-review/`}>Copilot Code Review</a> — an AI reviewer on every pull request</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}capabilities/agent-merge/`}>Agent Merge</a> — remediates findings and merges when checks are green</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}capabilities/github-actions/`}>GitHub Actions (CI/CD)</a> — builds, gates, and deploys</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}capabilities/security-review/`}>AI-assisted security review</a> — the supply-chain layer: dependencies, secrets, tokens</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}capabilities/lifecycle-automation/`}>End-to-end lifecycle automation</a> — the whole loop, running on every change</li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    See <a href={`${base}secure-supply-chain/`}>Secure your supply chain</a> for why the
    security beats in this demo live in dependencies and CI/CD, not just application code.
  </p>
</Layout>
